-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Dover Corp, Salesforce.com
-- 
-- Mon Apr 21, 2014 02:41AM EDT
-- None



April 21 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including American Electric Power Co, Dover Corp and Salesforce.com, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * American Electric Power Company <AEP.N>: ISI Group cuts to neutral from buy * Dover Corp <DOV.N>: Stifel cuts to hold from buy * Salesforce.com <CRM.N>: Pivotal cuts price target to $74 from $77  Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* American National Bankshares <AMNB.O>: KBW cuts target to $23 from $24; market perform * American Electric Power Company <AEP.N>: ISI Group cuts to neutral from buy * Calpine Corp <CPN.N>: ISI Group raises price target to $23.50 from $23; rating neutral * Dover Corp <DOV.N>: Stifel cuts to hold from buy * Fifth Third Bancorp <FITB.O>: BMO cuts price target to $23 from $24; rating outperform  * Salesforce.com Inc <CRM.N>: Pivotal cuts price target to $74 from $77; rating buy